issue.title: Auto Delete
issue.body:
Auto deletion of chatrooms after 2 weeks:

- Add Last Updated Column
- Anytime new user posts something, update that column
- Run script that:

```
get_all_rooms(sort=descending_date)
for room in all_rooms where date_last_used > two_weeks:
   delete_room()
```

issue.title: REQUEST: Auto censoring
issue.body:
Run every question through a back end process and make sure it is clean of harmful speech before posting.

May be a performance hit, but something to look into if the issue arises in the future.

issue.title: REQUEST: Create a How-To pop-up / help section
issue.body: Requested by beta testers. Site's minimalism is likable, but too foreign for first time users.

issue.title: Question editing
issue.body:
A user should be able to modify/delete the questions they've submitted! Use case:
- The question has only one upvote and the user who submitted the question no longer has that question (assumption: one upvote means nobody else in the room has that question)
- The user made a typo/wants to adjust the wording of their question

Possible issues with this: need to think carefully about the mechanics of this, such that a user's individual actions do not influence others (e.g. someone else in the room has the same question, did not upvote but is waiting for the question be answered when the OP deletes the question because he/she has figured it out). Another tricky issue with this: when question matching is implemented, what if two questions are merged because they match, then the OP of the original question changes it such that the two questions no longer would match?

issue.title: Question typing experience issues
issue.body:
Question submission should have two options:
1. Click to send (meaning Enter creates a new line and Ctrl+Enter or clicking Submit submits the question)
2. Enter to send (meaning that Enter submits the question and Ctrl+Enter creates a new line)
This is exactly what LinkedIn offers:
![image](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/12475811/25307016/bdd81730-274e-11e7-8488-39b4ee199898.png)

issue.title: UI
issue.body:
Move all of UI to: https://semantic-ui.com/

Unfortunately, current UI does not seem to be easily compatible with mobile.

Cannot use `px` or `vh` (viewport units) for mobile, so it may be easier to switch everything over to semantic.

issue.title: "Top" view not re-sorted until refresh
issue.body: I remember it being mentioned that we'd have a functionality like Google News to refresh the question bank (in particular for the "Top" view) after a certain idle time. It appears that this feature is still not there, right?
